briefdescription.para: Deinitializes the CEC peripheral registers to their default reset values.
Initializes the CEC peripheral according to the specified parameters in the CEC_InitStruct.

parameterdescription.para: pointer to an CEC_InitTypeDef structure that contains the configuration information for the specified CEC peripheral.

briefdescription.para: Enables or disables the specified CEC peripheral.

parameterdescription.para: new state of the CEC peripheral. This parameter can be: ENABLE or DISABLE.

briefdescription.para: Enables or disables the CEC interrupt.

parameterdescription.para: new state of the CEC interrupt. This parameter can be: ENABLE or DISABLE.

briefdescription.para: Defines the Own Address of the CEC device.
Transmits single data through the CEC peripheral.
Returns the most recent received data by the CEC peripheral.
Transmits message with or without an EOM bit.

parameterdescription.para: new state of the CEC Tx End Of Message. This parameter can be: ENABLE or DISABLE.

specifies the CEC flag to check. This parameter can be one of the following values:
CEC_FLAG_BTE: Bit Timing Error
CEC_FLAG_BPE: Bit Period Error
CEC_FLAG_RBTFE: Rx Block Transfer Finished Error
CEC_FLAG_SBE: Start Bit Error
CEC_FLAG_ACKE: Block Acknowledge Error
CEC_FLAG_LINE: Line Error
CEC_FLAG_TBTFE: Tx Block Transfer Finished Error
CEC_FLAG_TEOM: Tx End Of Message
CEC_FLAG_TERR: Tx Error
CEC_FLAG_TBTRF: Tx Byte Transfer Request or Block Transfer Finished
CEC_FLAG_RSOM: Rx Start Of Message
CEC_FLAG_REOM: Rx End Of Message
CEC_FLAG_RERR: Rx Error
CEC_FLAG_RBTF: Rx Byte/Block Transfer Finished
new state of CEC_FLAG (SET or RESET)

specifies the flag to clear. This parameter can be any combination of the following values:
CEC_FLAG_TERR: Tx Error
CEC_FLAG_TBTRF: Tx Byte Transfer Request or Block Transfer Finished
CEC_FLAG_RSOM: Rx Start Of Message
CEC_FLAG_REOM: Rx End Of Message
CEC_FLAG_RERR: Rx Error
CEC_FLAG_RBTF: Rx Byte/Block Transfer Finished

briefdescription.para: Checks whether the specified CEC interrupt has occurred or not.

parameterdescription.para:
specifies the CEC interrupt source to check. This parameter can be one of the following values:
CEC_IT_TERR: Tx Error
CEC_IT_TBTF: Tx Block Transfer Finished
CEC_IT_RERR: Rx Error
CEC_IT_RBTF: Rx Block Transfer Finished
new state of CEC_IT (SET or RESET).

briefdescription.para: Clears the CEC's interrupt pending bits.

parameterdescription.para:
specifies the CEC interrupt pending bit to clear. This parameter can be any combination of the following values:
CEC_IT_TERR: Tx Error
CEC_IT_TBTF: Tx Block Transfer Finished
CEC_IT_RERR: Rx Error
CEC_IT_RBTF: Rx Block Transfer Finished
